Privacy Policy

Bitcoin Price Checker is committed to protecting your privacy. This privacy policy outlines what information the extension collects, how it is used, and your rights regarding that information.

Data Collection
This extension does not collect, store, or share any personal data. It fetches Bitcoin price data from the CoinDesk API but does not transmit, store, or access user-related information.

Permissions
The extension may require the following permissions:

Access to the CoinDesk API: To fetch live Bitcoin price data, the extension makes secure fetch requests to the CoinDesk API. No user data is transmitted in this process.
Local Storage
The extension may store basic settings (e.g., user preferences) locally on your device to improve functionality. This data is not shared or transmitted to external servers.

Third-Party Services
The extension uses the CoinDesk API to fetch Bitcoin price data. You can review CoinDesk's privacy policy for more information about their data practices: CoinDesk Privacy Policy.

Data Sharing
The extension does not share any user data with third parties.

Security
All data fetching processes are secure and compliant with web standards. The extension operates within the Chrome Web Store's strict privacy and security policies.

Changes to this Policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be communicated through the Chrome Web Store listing.

Contact
If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy, please contact us at [your-email@example.com].

By using this extension, you agree to the terms of this privacy policy. Thank you for trusting Bitcoin Price Checker!
